<title>USA: IPO FILING-Logility Inc.</title>
<headline>IPO FILING-Logility Inc.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Company Name			Logility Inc</p>
<p>Stock symbol			LGTY.O</p>
<p>Estimated price range	   $11-$13/shr</p>
<p>Total shares to be offered    2.2 million</p>
<p>Shrs offered by company	 2.2 million</p>
<p>Shrs outstanding after ipo    13,500,000</p>
<p>Lead Underwriter    Montgomery Securities</p>
<p>Underwriters over-allotment  330,000 shrs Following this offer American Software Inc will own about 84 percent of the outstanding (assuming no exercise of the underwriters' over-allotment option). Logility is currently a wholly-owned subsidiary of American Software. Business: Logility, based in Atlanta, Ga., develops, markets and supports software applications that optimize the operating efficiencies of manufacturers, suppliers, distributors, retailers and other organizations along the &quot;value chain.&quot; Use of Proceeds: For research and development, sales and marketing, working capital and other general corporate purposes and possible acquisitions.</p>
</text>
